Antiviral prescribing model

Baseline parameters

  • Clinical attack rates are derived from the 2022/23 season burden estimates.
  • Percent who are prescribed antiviral neuraminidase inhibitors (NAIs) is informed by VISION, VE Network, and literature review
  • Care-seeking is informed by Outbreaks Near Me (ONM) and VE Network
  • Percent tested informed by VISION
  • Test sensitivity is informed by literature for molecular rapid tests.
  • Antiviral compliance is informed by ONM and the Respiratory Virus Transmission Network (RVTN)

Extreme scenarios vs baseline
